examples_key2: In this section, some examples are given. You need to understand these examples very carefully, to figure out how they work? You have to do a `dry run` of each of the examples and notice that how the dry run works.
examples_key3: You can also add some more examples as comments so that your, as well as your peer's concept, becomes clear.
examples_key5: You have to print multiples of 3 from 1 to 40. While writing the `code` keep in mind that the counter starts from 891.
examples_key8: Write a `code` to print all the multiples of 5 from 1 to 50. But you don't need to use % (modulus `operator`). Do without it.
examples_key11: Print all the odd numbers between 50 to 100.
examples_key16: Print the numbers from 1 to 10 without using increment.
